00:26:30,923 --> 00:26:32,963
Oh!  Again. Again. CROWD GROANS

454
00:26:32,963 --> 00:26:35,243
I spent the rest of the trip holed
up in a hotel room,

455
00:26:35,243 --> 00:26:37,443
sweating and shivering,
browsing the web.

456
00:26:37,443 --> 00:26:38,843
I bet you did.

457
00:26:38,843 --> 00:26:40,803
LAUGHING

458
00:26:40,803 --> 00:26:42,923
Well, there's plenty more of
Thailand still to see,

459
00:26:42,923 --> 00:26:45,003
and we'll get back to it later on in
the show.

460
00:26:45,003 --> 00:26:48,683
But first, there's a shiny
new electric supercar on the scene,

461
00:26:48,683 --> 00:26:51,643
and we told Chris Harris to pop
on his rubber wellies

462
00:26:51,643 --> 00:26:53,043
and go check it out.

463
00:27:03,123 --> 00:27:04,803
Here it is.

464
00:27:04,803 --> 00:27:07,523
It's called the Nevera.

465
00:27:07,523 --> 00:27:10,043
It's powered by electricity.

466
00:27:10,043 --> 00:27:13,123
And it doesn't come from Italy,

467
00:27:13,123 --> 00:27:14,603
or Germany,

468
00:27:14,603 --> 00:27:15,843
or Britain,

469
00:27:15,843 --> 00:27:17,403
or Japan,

470
00:27:17,403 --> 00:27:19,483
or even America.

471
00:27:19,483 --> 00:27:22,003
No, the Nevera comes...

472
00:27:23,043 --> 00:27:24,323
..from Croatia.

473
00:27:31,883 --> 00:27:33,443
Now, Croatia.

474
00:27:33,443 --> 00:27:36,683
Lovely place, cracking
seafood scene,

475
00:27:36,683 --> 00:27:40,523
but not one with any history
of building fast cars

476
00:27:40,523 --> 00:27:44,283
or any history of building any cars.

477
00:27:44,283 --> 00:27:49,123
But this Nevera could be the car
to put Croatia on the car map

478
00:27:49,123 --> 00:27:54,243
because it's built by a company
called Rimac.

479
00:27:54,243 --> 00:27:56,803
Rimac's barely a decade old,

480
00:27:56,803 --> 00:28:00,003
but it's already worked its
electric wizardry

481
00:28:00,003 --> 00:28:02,763
for the likes of Porsche,
Aston Martin,

482
00:28:02,763 --> 00:28:05,643
Ferrari and Koenigsegg.

483
00:28:05,643 --> 00:28:09,803
Last year, it took control
of Bugatti.

484
00:28:09,803 --> 00:28:12,803
In short, Rimac means business.

485
00:28:12,803 --> 00:28:17,683
And with the Nevera, it's very much
going it alone.

486
00:28:17,683 --> 00:28:21,643
See, normally if you're a start up
carmaker,

487
00:28:21,643 --> 00:28:24,483
you buy all your bits off the shelf.

488
00:28:24,483 --> 00:28:28,163
You get your headlights from Ford,
steering wheel from Volvo,

489
00:28:28,163 --> 00:28:29,843
engine from GM,

490
00:28:29,843 --> 00:28:32,923
and then you wrap it all in some
fancy new bodywork.

491
00:28:34,683 --> 00:28:36,883
But Rimac hasn't done that.

492
00:28:39,163 --> 00:28:42,523
The Nevera is built completely
from scratch.

493
00:28:43,643 --> 00:28:47,443
The only bits this car shares
with any other on the planet

494
00:28:47,443 --> 00:28:51,203
are the tyres and a few bits
of the aircon.

495
00:28:52,603 --> 00:28:56,523
Everything else - battery,
motors, software,

496
00:28:56,523 --> 00:29:00,923
single piece carbon fibre
chassis - is bespoke.

497
00:29:05,283 --> 00:29:09,243
As business plans go, that's like
opening your own pizzeria

498
00:29:09,243 --> 00:29:12,363
and decided that instead of buying
in any ingredients,

499
00:29:12,363 --> 00:29:15,723
you'll grow your own wheat,
your tomatoes,

500
00:29:15,723 --> 00:29:18,683
your pineapple, your buffalo.

501
00:29:18,683 --> 00:29:23,283
I mean, it's a ruinously stupid
idea, and it's why no-one does it.

502
00:29:23,283 --> 00:29:26,443
But somehow Rimac has made it work.

503
00:29:28,403 --> 00:29:30,123
And more remarkable still...

504
00:29:31,403 --> 00:29:35,283
..they've actually made it
rather well.

